<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="machine">Machine</a> - A set of parts that use energy to perform an action. A biological example is <a href="#transcription">transcriptional</a> machinery: a set of <a href="#protein">proteins</a> harness the energy of nucleotide triphosphate bonds to polymerize <a href="#rna">RNA</a> transcripts.